---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const webpageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation/#webpage',
  url: 'https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation',
  name: 'Enterprise AI Point of View | Chandra Kanojia',
  description: 'A practical point of view on enterprise AI, CRM, workflow, controls, evidence, and regulated operating change.',
  isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#website' },
  about: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#person' }
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://chandrakanojia.com' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Enterprise AI', item: 'https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation' }
  ]
};
---
<PageLayout
  title="Enterprise AI Point of View | Chandra Kanojia"
  description="A practical point of view on enterprise AI, CRM, workflow, controls, evidence, and regulated operating change."
  canonical="https://chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation"
  jsonLd={[webpageSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="ai-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="kicker">Enterprise AI Point of View</p>
      <h1 id="ai-title">AI is moving faster than the enterprise.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The serious work starts after the assistant. Large organizations are learning that better tools do not automatically change how work gets done.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="shift-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="kicker">The shift</p>
      <h2 id="shift-title">The question is no longer whether AI can help. The question is where it belongs.</h2>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        AI becomes useful when it lands inside the systems where work actually moves: CRM, case management, analytics, service platforms, approvals, controls, and leadership routines.
      </p>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        That is where the gap appears. The model may be capable. The enterprise may still need to redesign the work around it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt" aria-labelledby="board-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="board-memo">
        <p class="kicker">The board question</p>
        <h2 id="board-title">Can management change the work without weakening trust?</h2>
        <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          Leaders do not need another impressive demo. They need to know what evidence the AI used, what it is allowed to do, when a human returns, how the action is logged, and whether the result improved the business.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading compact-heading">
        <p class="kicker">Operating truths</p>
        <h2 id="principles-title">What survives beyond the demo.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="principles">
        <article class="principle"><p>The demo is the easy part. The hard part is changing how work moves.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>A fluent answer is not a reliable decision. The enterprise needs evidence discipline.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>Useful AI does not act everywhere. It acts where the permissions, controls, audit path, and escalation model are clear.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>The test is not the model. The test is cycle time, capacity, experience, risk, and business value.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="ai-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-box mandate-cta">
        <div>
          <p class="panel-label">Discuss the mandate</p>
          <h2 id="ai-cta">Useful conversations start where AI capability meets the operating model.</h2>
          <p>AI execution, CRM and workflow modernization, controlled action, adoption, platform reliability, and risk-aware operating leverage.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chandra-kanojia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
